<div class="page" data-ng-controller="HtmlCtrl" >
  <div class="constitute-html csection">
    <h1 class="clearfix">
    Syrian Arab Republic 2012
    
    
  
    
  
    
</h1>



  <div class="constitution-content" data-languages="en,es,ar">
<div class="constitution-topics"></div>
<div class="constitution-content__copy"><!--Section: section/0, type: -->
<div id="s0" data-link-target="s0" data-id="section/0" class="section"><!--Section: section/1, type: title-->
<div id="s1" data-link-target="s1" data-id="section/1" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="preamble">Preamble</span>
</div>
<h2 class="upper depth-0">Preamble</h2><!--Section: section/2, type: body-->
<div id="s2" data-link-target="s2" data-id="section/2" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">Arab civilization, which is part of human heritage, has faced through its long history great challenges aimed at breaking its will and subjecting it to colonial domination, but it has always rose through its own creative abilities to exercise its role in building human civilization.</p></div><!--Section: section/3, type: body-->
<div id="s3" data-link-target="s3" data-id="section/3" class="section article-list level1 article-body">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="region">Regional group(s)</span>
</div><p class="content">The Syrian Arab Republic is proud of its Arab identity and the fact that its people are an integral part of the Arab nation. The Syrian Arab Republic embodies this belonging in its national and pan-Arab project and the work to support Arab cooperation in order to promote integration and achieve the unity of the Arab nation.</p></div><!--Section: section/4, type: body-->
<div id="s4" data-link-target="s4" data-id="section/4" class="section article-list level1 article-body">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="intlaw">International law</span>
</div><p class="content">The Syrian Arab Republic considers international peace and security a key objective and a strategic choice, and it works on achieving both of them under the International Law and the values of right and justice.</p></div><!--Section: section/5, type: body-->
<div id="s5" data-link-target="s5" data-id="section/5" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">The Syrian Arab role has increased on the regional and international levels over the past decades, which has led to achieving human and national aspirations and achievements in all fields and domains. Syria has occupied an important political position as it is the beating heart of Arabism, the forefront of confrontation with the Zionist enemy and the bedrock of resistance against colonial hegemony on the Arab world and its capabilities and wealth. The long struggle and sacrifices of our people for the sake of its independence, progress and national unity has paved the way for building the strong state and promoting cohesion between the people and their Syrian Arab army which is the main guarantor and protector of the homeland’s sovereignty, security, stability and territorial integrity; thus, forming the solid foundation of the people’s struggle for liberating all occupied territories.</p></div><!--Section: section/6, type: body-->
<div id="s6" data-link-target="s6" data-id="section/6" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">The Syrian society with all its components and constituents and through its popular, political and civil institutions and organizations, has managed to accomplish achievements that demonstrated the depth of civilizational accumulation represented by the Syrian society, its unwavering will and its ability to keep pace with the changes and to create the appropriate environment to maintain its human role as a historical and effective power in the march of human civilization.</p></div><!--Section: section/7, type: body-->
<div id="s7" data-link-target="s7" data-id="section/7" class="section article-list level1 article-body">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="prevcond">Reference to country's history</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="motive">Motives for writing constitution</span>
</div><p class="content">Since the beginning of the 21st century, Syria, both as people and institutions had faced the challenge of development and modernization during tough regional and international circumstances which targeted its national sovereignty. This has formed the incentive to accomplish this Constitution as the basis for strengthening the rule of law.</p></div><!--Section: section/8, type: body-->
<div id="s8" data-link-target="s8" data-id="section/8" class="section article-list level1 article-body">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="motive">Motives for writing constitution</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="dignity">Human dignity</span>
</div><p class="content">The completion of this Constitution is the culmination of the people’s struggle on the road to freedom and democracy. It is a real embodiment of achievements, a response to shifts and changes, an evidence of organizing the march of the state towards the future, a regulator of the movement of its institutions and a source of legislation. All of this is attainable through a system of fundamental principles that enshrines independence, sovereignty and the rule of the people based on election, political and party pluralism and the protection of national unity, cultural diversity, public freedoms, human rights, social justice, equality, equal opportunities, citizenship and the rule of law, where the society and the citizen are the objective and purpose for which every national effort is dedicated. Preserving the dignity of the society and the citizen is an indicator of the civilization of the country and the prestige of the state.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/9, type: title-->
<div id="s9" data-link-target="s9" data-id="section/9" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">Title I. Basic Principles</h3><!--Section: section/10, type: title-->
<div id="s10" data-link-target="s10" data-id="section/10" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Chapter I. Political Principles</h3><!--Section: section/11, type: title-->
<div id="s11" data-link-target="s11" data-id="section/11" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="region">Regional group(s)</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 1</h3><!--Section: section/12, type: body-->
<div id="s12" data-link-target="s12" data-id="section/12" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The Syrian Arab Republic is a democratic state with full sovereignty, indivisible, and may not waive any part of its territory, and is part of the Arab homeland; The people of Syria are part of the Arab nation.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/13, type: title-->
<div id="s13" data-link-target="s13" data-id="section/13" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="system">Type of government envisioned</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 2</h3><!--Section: section/14, type: body-->
<div id="s14" data-link-target="s14" data-id="section/14" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The system of governance in the state shall be a republican system; Sovereignty is an attribute of the people; and no individual or group may claim sovereignty. Sovereignty shall be based on the principle of the rule of the people by the people and for the people; The People shall exercise their sovereignty within the aspects and limits prescribed in the Constitution.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/15, type: title-->
<div id="s15" data-link-target="s15" data-id="section/15" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="rellaw">Status of religious law</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="freerel">Freedom of religion</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="offrel">Official religion</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hosrest">Eligibility for head of state</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 3</h3><!--Section: section/16, type: body-->
<div id="s16" data-link-target="s16" data-id="section/16" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The religion of the President of the Republic is Islam; Islamic jurisprudence shall be a major source of legislation; The State shall respect all religions, and ensure the freedom to perform all the rituals that do not prejudice public order; The personal status of religious communities shall be protected and respected.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/17, type: title-->
<div id="s17" data-link-target="s17" data-id="section/17" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="lang">Official or national languages</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 4</h3><!--Section: section/18, type: body-->
<div id="s18" data-link-target="s18" data-id="section/18" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The official language of the state is Arabic.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/19, type: title-->
<div id="s19" data-link-target="s19" data-id="section/19" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="capital">National capital</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 5</h3><!--Section: section/20, type: body-->
<div id="s20" data-link-target="s20" data-id="section/20" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The capital of the state is Damascus.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/21, type: title-->
<div id="s21" data-link-target="s21" data-id="section/21" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="flag">National flag</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="anthem">National anthem</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 6</h3><!--Section: section/22, type: body-->
<div id="s22" data-link-target="s22" data-id="section/22" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The flag of the Syrian Arab Republic consists of three colors: red, white and black, in addition to two stars, each with five heads of green color. The flag is rectangular in shape; its width equals two thirds of its length and consists of three rectangles evenly spaced along the flag, the highest in red, the middle in white and lowest in black, and the two stars are in the middle of the white rectangle; The law identifies the state’s emblem, its national anthem and the respective provisions.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/23, type: title-->
<div id="s23" data-link-target="s23" data-id="section/23" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="god">God or other deities</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="oath">Oaths to abide by constitution</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 7</h3><!--Section: section/24, type: body-->
<div id="s24" data-link-target="s24" data-id="section/24" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The constitutional oath shall be as follows: “I swear by the Almighty God to respect the country’s constitution, laws and Republican system, to look after the interests and freedoms of the people, to safeguard the homeland’s sovereignty, independence, freedom and to defend its territorial integrity and to act in order to achieve social justice and the unity of the Arab Nation”.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/25, type: title-->
<div id="s25" data-link-target="s25" data-id="section/25" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="partreg">Restrictions on political parties</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 8</h3><!--Section: section/26, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s26" data-link-target="s26" data-id="section/26" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The political system of the state shall be based on the principle of political pluralism, and exercising power democratically through the ballot box;</li><!--Section: section/28, type: list-->
<li id="s28" data-link-target="s28" data-id="section/28" style="list-style-type: '2. '">Licensed political parties and constituencies shall contribute to the national political life, and shall respect the principles of national sovereignty and democracy;</li><!--Section: section/30, type: list-->
<li id="s30" data-link-target="s30" data-id="section/30" style="list-style-type: '3. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="partrght">Right to form political parties</span>
</div>The law shall regulate the provisions and procedures related to the formation of political parties;</li><!--Section: section/32, type: list-->
<li id="s32" data-link-target="s32" data-id="section/32" style="list-style-type: '4. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="partprh">Prohibited political parties</span>
</div>Carrying out any political activity or forming any political parties or groupings on the basis of religious, sectarian, tribal, regional, class-based, professional, or on discrimination based on gender, origin, race or color may not be undertaken;</li><!--Section: section/34, type: list-->
<li id="s34" data-link-target="s34" data-id="section/34" style="list-style-type: '5. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="camppubf">Campaign financing</span>
</div>Public office or public money may not be exploited for a political, electoral or party interest.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/36, type: title-->
<div id="s36" data-link-target="s36" data-id="section/36" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cultrght">Right to culture</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 9</h3><!--Section: section/37, type: body-->
<div id="s37" data-link-target="s37" data-id="section/37" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">As a national heritage that promotes national unity in the framework of territorial integrity of the Syrian Arab Republic, the Constitution shall guarantee the protection of cultural diversity of the Syrian society with all its components and the multiplicity of its tributaries.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/38, type: title-->
<div id="s38" data-link-target="s38" data-id="section/38" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="assoc">Freedom of association</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="jointrde">Right to join trade unions</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 10</h3><!--Section: section/39, type: body-->
<div id="s39" data-link-target="s39" data-id="section/39" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Public organizations, professional unions and associations shall be bodies that group citizens in order to develop society and attain the interests of its members. The State shall guarantee the independence of these bodies and the right to exercise public control and participation in various sectors and councils defined in laws; in areas which achieve their objectives, and in accordance with the terms and conditions prescribed by law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/40, type: title-->
<div id="s40" data-link-target="s40" data-id="section/40" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 11</h3><!--Section: section/41, type: body-->
<div id="s41" data-link-target="s41" data-id="section/41" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The army and the armed forces shall be a national institution responsible for defending the security of the homeland and its territorial integrity. This institution shall be in the service of the people’s interests and the protection of its objectives and national security.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/42, type: title-->
<div id="s42" data-link-target="s42" data-id="section/42" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="mun">Municipal government</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 12</h3><!--Section: section/43, type: body-->
<div id="s43" data-link-target="s43" data-id="section/43" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Democratically elected councils at the national or local level shall be institutions through which citizens exercise their role in sovereignty, state-building and leading society.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/44, type: title-->
<div id="s44" data-link-target="s44" data-id="section/44" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Chapter II. Economic Principles</h3><!--Section: section/45, type: title-->
<div id="s45" data-link-target="s45" data-id="section/45" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 13</h3><!--Section: section/46, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s46" data-link-target="s46" data-id="section/46" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="econplan">Economic plans</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="standliv">Right to reasonable standard of living</span>
</div>The national economy shall be based on the principle of developing public and private economic activity through economic and social plans aiming at increasing the national income, developing production, raising the individual’s living standards and creating jobs;</li><!--Section: section/48, type: list-->
<li id="s48" data-link-target="s48" data-id="section/48" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="socclas">Mentions of social class</span>
</div>Economic policy of the state shall aim at meeting the basic needs of individuals and society through the achievement of economic growth and social justice in order to reach comprehensive, balanced and sustainable development;</li><!--Section: section/50, type: list-->
<li id="s50" data-link-target="s50" data-id="section/50" style="list-style-type: '3. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="freecomp">Right to competitive marketplace</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="conright">Protection of consumers</span>
</div>The State shall guarantee the protection of producers and consumers, foster trade and investment, prevent monopoly in various economic fields and work on developing human resources and protecting the labor force in a way that serves the national economy.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/52, type: title-->
<div id="s52" data-link-target="s52" data-id="section/52" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="env">Protection of environment</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="resrce">Ownership of natural resources</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 14</h3><!--Section: section/53, type: body-->
<div id="s53" data-link-target="s53" data-id="section/53" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Natural resources, facilities, institutions and public utilities shall be publicly owned, and the state shall invest and oversee their management for the benefit of all people, and the citizens’ duty is to protect them.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/54, type: title-->
<div id="s54" data-link-target="s54" data-id="section/54" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="exprop">Protection from expropriation</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="proprght">Right to own property</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 15</h3><!--Section: section/55, type: body-->
<div id="s55" data-link-target="s55" data-id="section/55" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Collective and individual private ownership shall be protected in accordance with the following basis:</p><!--Section: section/56, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s56" data-link-target="s56" data-id="section/56" style="list-style-type: '1. '">General confiscation of funds shall be prohibited;<!--Section: section/58, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s58" data-link-target="s58" data-id="section/58" style="list-style-type: 'a. '">Private ownership shall not be removed except in the public interest by a decree and against fair compensation according to the law;</li><!--Section: section/60, type: list-->
<li id="s60" data-link-target="s60" data-id="section/60" style="list-style-type: 'b. '">Confiscation of private property shall not be imposed without a final court ruling;</li><!--Section: section/62, type: list-->
<li id="s62" data-link-target="s62" data-id="section/62" style="list-style-type: 'c. '">Private property may be confiscated for necessities of war and disasters by a law and against fair compensation;</li></ol></li><!--Section: section/64, type: list-->
<li id="s64" data-link-target="s64" data-id="section/64" style="list-style-type: '2. '">Compensation shall be equivalent to the real value of the property.</li></ol></div>
</div><!--Section: section/66, type: title-->
<div id="s66" data-link-target="s66" data-id="section/66" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 16</h3><!--Section: section/67, type: body-->
<div id="s67" data-link-target="s67" data-id="section/67" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The law shall determine the maximum level of agricultural ownership and agricultural investment to ensure the protection of the farmer and the agricultural laborer from exploitation and to ensure increased production.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/68, type: title-->
<div id="s68" data-link-target="s68" data-id="section/68" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="transfer">Right to transfer property</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 17</h3><!--Section: section/69, type: body-->
<div id="s69" data-link-target="s69" data-id="section/69" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The right of inheritance shall be maintained in accordance with the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/70, type: title-->
<div id="s70" data-link-target="s70" data-id="section/70" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 18</h3><!--Section: section/71, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s71" data-link-target="s71" data-id="section/71" style="list-style-type: '1. '">Taxes, fees and overhead costs shall not be imposed except by a law;</li><!--Section: section/73, type: list-->
<li id="s73" data-link-target="s73" data-id="section/73" style="list-style-type: '2. '">The tax system shall be based on a fair basis; and taxes shall be progressive in a way that achieves the principles of equality and social justice.</li></ol></div>
</div><!--Section: section/75, type: title-->
<div id="s75" data-link-target="s75" data-id="section/75" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Chapter III. Social Principles</h3><!--Section: section/76, type: title-->
<div id="s76" data-link-target="s76" data-id="section/76" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="dignity">Human dignity</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="solid">Reference to fraternity/solidarity</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 19</h3><!--Section: section/77, type: body-->
<div id="s77" data-link-target="s77" data-id="section/77" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Society in the Syrian Arab Republic shall be based on the basis of solidarity, symbiosis and respect for the principles of social justice, freedom, equality and maintenance of human dignity of every individual.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/78, type: title-->
<div id="s78" data-link-target="s78" data-id="section/78" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 20</h3><!--Section: section/79, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s79" data-link-target="s79" data-id="section/79" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="fndfam">Right to found a family</span>
</div>The family shall be the nucleus of society and the law shall maintain its existence and strengthen its ties;</li><!--Section: section/81, type: list-->
<li id="s81" data-link-target="s81" data-id="section/81" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="marriage">Regulation of marriage</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="childpro">Rights of children</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="finsup4">State support for children</span>
</div>The state shall protect and encourage marriage, and shall work on removing material and social obstacles that hinder it. The state shall also protect maternity and childhood, take care of young children and youth and provide the suitable conditions for the development of their talents.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/83, type: title-->
<div id="s83" data-link-target="s83" data-id="section/83" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 21</h3><!--Section: section/84, type: body-->
<div id="s84" data-link-target="s84" data-id="section/84" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Martyrdom for the sake of the homeland shall be a supreme value, and the State shall guarantee the families of the martyrs in accordance with the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/85, type: title-->
<div id="s85" data-link-target="s85" data-id="section/85" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 22</h3><!--Section: section/86, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s86" data-link-target="s86" data-id="section/86" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="finsup4">State support for children</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="finsup3">State support for the disabled</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="finsup1">State support for the elderly</span>
</div>The state shall guarantee every citizen and his family in cases of emergency, sickness, disability, orphan-hood and old age;</li><!--Section: section/88, type: list-->
<li id="s88" data-link-target="s88" data-id="section/88" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="health">Right to health care</span>
</div>The state shall protect the health of citizens and provide them with the means of prevention, treatment and medication.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/90, type: title-->
<div id="s90" data-link-target="s90" data-id="section/90" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="opgroup">Provisions for wealth redistribution</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 23</h3><!--Section: section/91, type: body-->
<div id="s91" data-link-target="s91" data-id="section/91" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The state shall provide women with all opportunities enabling them to effectively and fully contribute to the political, economic, social and cultural life, and the state shall work on removing the restrictions that prevent their development and participation in building society.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/92, type: title-->
<div id="s92" data-link-target="s92" data-id="section/92" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="solid">Reference to fraternity/solidarity</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 24</h3><!--Section: section/93, type: body-->
<div id="s93" data-link-target="s93" data-id="section/93" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The state shall shoulder, in solidarity with the community, the burdens resulting from natural disasters.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/94, type: title-->
<div id="s94" data-link-target="s94" data-id="section/94" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="socclas">Mentions of social class</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 25</h3><!--Section: section/95, type: body-->
<div id="s95" data-link-target="s95" data-id="section/95" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Education, health and social services shall be the basic pillars for building society, and the state shall work on achieving balanced development among all regions of the Syrian Arab Republic.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/96, type: title-->
<div id="s96" data-link-target="s96" data-id="section/96" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="civil">Civil service recruitment</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 26</h3><!--Section: section/97, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s97" data-link-target="s97" data-id="section/97" style="list-style-type: '1. '">Public service shall be a responsibility and an honor the purpose of which is to achieve public interest and to serve the people;</li><!--Section: section/99, type: list-->
<li id="s99" data-link-target="s99" data-id="section/99" style="list-style-type: '2. '">Citizens shall be equal in assuming the functions of public service, and the law shall determine the conditions of assuming such functions and the rights and duties assigned to them.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/101, type: title-->
<div id="s101" data-link-target="s101" data-id="section/101" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="env">Protection of environment</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 27</h3><!--Section: section/102, type: body-->
<div id="s102" data-link-target="s102" data-id="section/102" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Protection of the environment shall be the responsibility of the state and society and it shall be the duty of every citizen.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/103, type: title-->
<div id="s103" data-link-target="s103" data-id="section/103" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Chapter IV. Educational and Cultural Principles</h3><!--Section: section/104, type: title-->
<div id="s104" data-link-target="s104" data-id="section/104" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 28</h3><!--Section: section/105, type: body-->
<div id="s105" data-link-target="s105" data-id="section/105" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The educational system shall be based on creating a generation committed to its identity, heritage, belonging and national unity.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/106, type: title-->
<div id="s106" data-link-target="s106" data-id="section/106" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 29</h3><!--Section: section/107, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s107" data-link-target="s107" data-id="section/107" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="edfree">Free education</span>
</div>Education shall be a right guaranteed by the state, and it is free at all levels. The law shall regulate the cases where education could not be free at universities and government institutes;</li><!--Section: section/109, type: list-->
<li id="s109" data-link-target="s109" data-id="section/109" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="edcomp">Compulsory education</span>
</div>Education shall be compulsory until the end of basic education stage, and the state shall work on extending compulsory education to other stages;</li><!--Section: section/111, type: list-->
<li id="s111" data-link-target="s111" data-id="section/111" style="list-style-type: '3. '">The state shall oversee education and direct it in a way that achieves the link between it and the needs of society and the requirements of development;</li><!--Section: section/113, type: list-->
<li id="s113" data-link-target="s113" data-id="section/113" style="list-style-type: '4. '">The law shall regulate the state’s supervision of private educational institutions.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/115, type: title-->
<div id="s115" data-link-target="s115" data-id="section/115" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 30</h3><!--Section: section/116, type: body-->
<div id="s116" data-link-target="s116" data-id="section/116" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Physical education shall be an essential pillar in building society; and the state shall encourage it to prepare a generation which is physically, morally and intellectually fit.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/117, type: title-->
<div id="s117" data-link-target="s117" data-id="section/117" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="artists">Reference to art</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="science">Reference to science</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="acfree">Right to academic freedom</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="intprop">Provisions for intellectual property</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 31</h3><!--Section: section/118, type: body-->
<div id="s118" data-link-target="s118" data-id="section/118" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The state shall support scientific research and all its requirements, ensure the freedom of scientific, literary, artistic and cultural creativity and provide the necessary means for that end. The state shall provide any assistance for the progress of sciences and arts, and shall encourage scientific and technical inventions, creative skills and talents and protect their results.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/119, type: title-->
<div id="s119" data-link-target="s119" data-id="section/119" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cultrght">Right to culture</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="artists">Reference to art</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 32</h3><!--Section: section/120, type: body-->
<div id="s120" data-link-target="s120" data-id="section/120" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The state shall protect antiquities, archaeological and heritage sites and objects of artistic, historical and cultural value.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/121, type: title-->
<div id="s121" data-link-target="s121" data-id="section/121" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">Title II. Rights, Freedoms and the Rule of Law</h3><!--Section: section/122, type: title-->
<div id="s122" data-link-target="s122" data-id="section/122" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Chapter I. Rights and Freedoms</h3><!--Section: section/123, type: title-->
<div id="s123" data-link-target="s123" data-id="section/123" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 33</h3><!--Section: section/124, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s124" data-link-target="s124" data-id="section/124" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="dignity">Human dignity</span>
</div>Freedom shall be a sacred right and the state shall guarantee the personal freedom of citizens and preserve their dignity and security;</li><!--Section: section/126, type: list-->
<li id="s126" data-link-target="s126" data-id="section/126" style="list-style-type: '2. '">Citizenship shall be a fundamental principle which involves rights and duties enjoyed by every citizen and exercised according to law;</li><!--Section: section/128, type: list-->
<li id="s128" data-link-target="s128" data-id="section/128" style="list-style-type: '3. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="equalgr5">Equality regardless of language</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="equalgr11">Equality regardless of creed or belief</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="equal">General guarantee of equality</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="equalgr3">Equality regardless of origin</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="equalgr6">Equality regardless of religion</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="equalgr1">Equality regardless of gender</span>
</div>Citizens shall be equal in rights and duties without discrimination among them on grounds of sex, origin, language, religion or creed;</li><!--Section: section/130, type: list-->
<li id="s130" data-link-target="s130" data-id="section/130" style="list-style-type: '4. '">The state shall guarantee the principle of equal opportunities among citizens.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/132, type: title-->
<div id="s132" data-link-target="s132" data-id="section/132" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cultrght">Right to culture</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 34</h3><!--Section: section/133, type: body-->
<div id="s133" data-link-target="s133" data-id="section/133" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Every citizen shall have the right to participate in the political, economic, social and cultural life and the law shall regulate this.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/134, type: title-->
<div id="s134" data-link-target="s134" data-id="section/134" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="abide">Duty to obey the constitution</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 35</h3><!--Section: section/135, type: body-->
<div id="s135" data-link-target="s135" data-id="section/135" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Every citizen shall be subjected to the duty of respecting the Constitution and laws.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/136, type: title-->
<div id="s136" data-link-target="s136" data-id="section/136" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="privacy">Right to privacy</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 36</h3><!--Section: section/137, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s137" data-link-target="s137" data-id="section/137" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="inalrght">Inalienable rights</span>
</div>The inviolability of private life shall be protected by the law;</li><!--Section: section/139, type: list-->
<li id="s139" data-link-target="s139" data-id="section/139" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="evidence">Regulation of evidence collection</span>
</div>Houses shall not be entered or inspected except by an order of the competent judicial authority in the cases prescribed by law.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/141, type: title-->
<div id="s141" data-link-target="s141" data-id="section/141" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="privacy">Right to privacy</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="telecom">Telecommunications</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="radio">Radio</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 37</h3><!--Section: section/142, type: body-->
<div id="s142" data-link-target="s142" data-id="section/142" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Confidentiality of postal correspondence, telecommunications and radio and other communication shall be guaranteed in accordance with the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/143, type: title-->
<div id="s143" data-link-target="s143" data-id="section/143" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="resenex">Restrictions on entry or exit</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 38</h3><!--Section: section/144, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s144" data-link-target="s144" data-id="section/144" style="list-style-type: '1. '">No citizen may be deported from the country, or prevented from returning to it;</li><!--Section: section/146, type: list-->
<li id="s146" data-link-target="s146" data-id="section/146" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="excrim">Extradition procedure</span>
</div>No citizen may be extradited to any foreign entity;</li><!--Section: section/148, type: list-->
<li id="s148" data-link-target="s148" data-id="section/148" style="list-style-type: '3. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="freemove">Freedom of movement</span>
</div>Every citizen shall have the right to move in or leave the territory of the state, unless prevented by a decision from the competent court or the public prosecution office or in accordance with the laws of public health and safety.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/150, type: title-->
<div id="s150" data-link-target="s150" data-id="section/150" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="excrim">Extradition procedure</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="asylum">Protection of stateless persons</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 39</h3><!--Section: section/151, type: body-->
<div id="s151" data-link-target="s151" data-id="section/151" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Political refugees shall not be extradited because of their political beliefs or for their defense of freedom.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/152, type: title-->
<div id="s152" data-link-target="s152" data-id="section/152" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 40</h3><!--Section: section/153, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s153" data-link-target="s153" data-id="section/153" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="work">Duty to work</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="provwork">Right to work</span>
</div>Work shall be a right and a duty for every citizen, and the state shall endeavor to provide for all citizens, and the law shall organize work, its conditions and the workers’ rights;</li><!--Section: section/155, type: list-->
<li id="s155" data-link-target="s155" data-id="section/155" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="remuner">Right to just remuneration</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="standliv">Right to reasonable standard of living</span>
</div>Each worker shall have a fair wage according to the quality and output of the work; this wage shall be no less than the minimum wage that ensures the requirements of living and changes in living conditions;</li><!--Section: section/157, type: list-->
<li id="s157" data-link-target="s157" data-id="section/157" style="list-style-type: '3. '">The state shall guarantee social and health security of workers.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/159, type: title-->
<div id="s159" data-link-target="s159" data-id="section/159" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="taxes">Duty to pay taxes</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 41</h3><!--Section: section/160, type: body-->
<div id="s160" data-link-target="s160" data-id="section/160" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Payment of taxes, fees and public costs shall be a duty in accordance with the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/161, type: title-->
<div id="s161" data-link-target="s161" data-id="section/161" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 42</h3><!--Section: section/162, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s162" data-link-target="s162" data-id="section/162" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="opinion">Freedom of opinion/thought/conscience</span>
</div>Freedom of belief shall be protected in accordance with the law;</li><!--Section: section/164, type: list-->
<li id="s164" data-link-target="s164" data-id="section/164" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="express">Freedom of expression</span>
</div>Every citizen shall have the right to freely and openly express his views whether in writing or orally or by all other means of expression.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/166, type: title-->
<div id="s166" data-link-target="s166" data-id="section/166" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="press">Freedom of press</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 43</h3><!--Section: section/167, type: body-->
<div id="s167" data-link-target="s167" data-id="section/167" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The state shall guarantee freedom of the press, printing and publishing, the media and its independence in accordance with the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/168, type: title-->
<div id="s168" data-link-target="s168" data-id="section/168" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="strike">Right to strike</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="assem">Freedom of assembly</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 44</h3><!--Section: section/169, type: body-->
<div id="s169" data-link-target="s169" data-id="section/169" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Citizens shall have the right to assemble, peacefully demonstrate and to strike from work within the framework of the Constitution principles, and the law shall regulate the exercise of these rights.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/170, type: title-->
<div id="s170" data-link-target="s170" data-id="section/170" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="jointrde">Right to join trade unions</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="assoc">Freedom of association</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 45</h3><!--Section: section/171, type: body-->
<div id="s171" data-link-target="s171" data-id="section/171" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Freedom of forming associations and unions shall be based on a patriotic basis, for lawful purposes and by peaceful means which are guaranteed in accordance with the terms and conditions prescribed by law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/172, type: title-->
<div id="s172" data-link-target="s172" data-id="section/172" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="milserv">Duty to serve in the military</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 46</h3><!--Section: section/173, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s173" data-link-target="s173" data-id="section/173" style="list-style-type: '1. '">Compulsory military service shall be a sacred duty and is regulated by a law;</li><!--Section: section/175, type: list-->
<li id="s175" data-link-target="s175" data-id="section/175" style="list-style-type: '2. '">Defending the territorial integrity of the homeland and maintaining the secrets of state shall be a duty of every citizen.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/177, type: title-->
<div id="s177" data-link-target="s177" data-id="section/177" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 47</h3><!--Section: section/178, type: body-->
<div id="s178" data-link-target="s178" data-id="section/178" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The state shall guarantee the protection of national unity, and the citizens’ duty is to maintain it.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/179, type: title-->
<div id="s179" data-link-target="s179" data-id="section/179" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="citizen">Requirements for birthright citizenship</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 48</h3><!--Section: section/180, type: body-->
<div id="s180" data-link-target="s180" data-id="section/180" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The law shall regulate the Syrian Arab citizenship.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/181, type: title-->
<div id="s181" data-link-target="s181" data-id="section/181" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="referen">Referenda</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 49</h3><!--Section: section/182, type: body-->
<div id="s182" data-link-target="s182" data-id="section/182" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Election and referendum are the right and duty of the citizens and the law shall regulate their exercise.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/183, type: title-->
<div id="s183" data-link-target="s183" data-id="section/183" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Chapter II. The Rule of Law</h3><!--Section: section/184, type: title-->
<div id="s184" data-link-target="s184" data-id="section/184" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 50</h3><!--Section: section/185, type: body-->
<div id="s185" data-link-target="s185" data-id="section/185" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The rule of law shall be the basis of governance in the state.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/186, type: title-->
<div id="s186" data-link-target="s186" data-id="section/186" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 51</h3><!--Section: section/187, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s187" data-link-target="s187" data-id="section/187" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="wolaw">Principle of no punishment without law</span>
</div>Punishment shall be personal; no crime and no punishment except by a law;</li><!--Section: section/189, type: list-->
<li id="s189" data-link-target="s189" data-id="section/189" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="fairtri">Right to fair trial</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="presinoc">Presumption of innocence in trials</span>
</div>Every defendant shall be presumed innocent until convicted by a final court ruling in a fair trial;</li><!--Section: section/191, type: list-->
<li id="s191" data-link-target="s191" data-id="section/191" style="list-style-type: '3. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="couns">Right to counsel</span>
</div>The right to conduct litigation and remedies, review, and the defense before the judiciary shall be protected by the law, and the state shall guarantee legal aid to those who are incapable to do so, in accordance with the law;</li><!--Section: section/193, type: list-->
<li id="s193" data-link-target="s193" data-id="section/193" style="list-style-type: '4. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="illadmin">Ultra-vires administrative actions</span>
</div>Any provision of the law shall prohibit the immunity of any act or administrative decision from judicial review.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/195, type: title-->
<div id="s195" data-link-target="s195" data-id="section/195" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="expost">Protection from ex post facto laws</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 52</h3><!--Section: section/196, type: body-->
<div id="s196" data-link-target="s196" data-id="section/196" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Provisions of the laws shall only apply to the date of its commencement and shall not have a retroactive effect, and it may apply otherwise in matters other than criminal.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/197, type: title-->
<div id="s197" data-link-target="s197" data-id="section/197" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 53</h3><!--Section: section/198, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s198" data-link-target="s198" data-id="section/198" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="habcorp">Protection from unjustified restraint</span>
</div>No one may be investigated or arrested, except under an order or decision issued by the competent judicial authority, or if he was arrested in the case of being caught in the act, or with intent to bring him to the judicial authorities on charges of committing a felony or misdemeanor;</li><!--Section: section/200, type: list-->
<li id="s200" data-link-target="s200" data-id="section/200" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cruelty">Prohibition of cruel treatment</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="torture">Prohibition of torture</span>
</div>No one may be tortured or treated in a humiliating manner, and the law shall define the punishment for those who do so;</li><!--Section: section/202, type: list-->
<li id="s202" data-link-target="s202" data-id="section/202" style="list-style-type: '3. '">Any person who is arrested must be informed of the reasons for his arrest and his rights, and may not be incarcerated in front of the administrative authority except by an order of the competent judicial authority;</li><!--Section: section/204, type: list-->
<li id="s204" data-link-target="s204" data-id="section/204" style="list-style-type: '4. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="falseimp">Protection from false imprisonment</span>
</div>Every person sentenced by a final ruling, carried out his sentence and the ruling proved wrong shall have the right to ask the state for compensation for the damage he suffered.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/206, type: title-->
<div id="s206" data-link-target="s206" data-id="section/206" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="inalrght">Inalienable rights</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 54</h3><!--Section: section/207, type: body-->
<div id="s207" data-link-target="s207" data-id="section/207" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Any assault on individual freedom, on the inviolability of private life or any other rights and public freedoms guaranteed by the Constitution shall be considered a punishable crime by the law.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/208, type: title-->
<div id="s208" data-link-target="s208" data-id="section/208" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">Title III. State Authorities</h3><!--Section: section/209, type: title-->
<div id="s209" data-link-target="s209" data-id="section/209" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Chapter I. Legislative Authority</h3><!--Section: section/210, type: title-->
<div id="s210" data-link-target="s210" data-id="section/210" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="housenum">Structure of legislative chamber(s)</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 55</h3><!--Section: section/211, type: body-->
<div id="s211" data-link-target="s211" data-id="section/211" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The legislative authority of the state shall be assumed by the People’s Assembly in accordance with the manner prescribed in the Constitution.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/212, type: title-->
<div id="s212" data-link-target="s212" data-id="section/212" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="lhterm">Term length for first chamber</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 56</h3><!--Section: section/213, type: body-->
<div id="s213" data-link-target="s213" data-id="section/213" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The People’s Assembly term shall be for four calendar years from the date of its first meeting and it may not be extended except in case of war by a law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/214, type: title-->
<div id="s214" data-link-target="s214" data-id="section/214" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="freeelec">Secret ballot</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="lhselect">First chamber selection</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 57</h3><!--Section: section/215, type: body-->
<div id="s215" data-link-target="s215" data-id="section/215" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Members of the People’s Assembly shall be elected by the public, secret, direct and equal vote in accordance with the provisions of the Election Law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/216, type: title-->
<div id="s216" data-link-target="s216" data-id="section/216" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 58</h3><!--Section: section/217, type: body-->
<div id="s217" data-link-target="s217" data-id="section/217" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">A member of the People’s Assembly shall represent the whole people, and his/her commission may not be defined by a restriction or condition, and shall exercise duties under the guidance of his/hers honor and conscience.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/218, type: title-->
<div id="s218" data-link-target="s218" data-id="section/218" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="voteres">Restrictions on voting</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 59</h3><!--Section: section/219, type: body-->
<div id="s219" data-link-target="s219" data-id="section/219" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Voters shall be the citizens who have completed eighteen years of age and met the conditions stipulated in the Election Law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/220, type: title-->
<div id="s220" data-link-target="s220" data-id="section/220" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="lhrest">Eligibility for first chamber</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 60</h3><!--Section: section/221, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s221" data-link-target="s221" data-id="section/221" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="lhseats">Size of first chamber</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="lhselect">First chamber selection</span>
</div>The system of electing members of the People’s Assembly, their number and the conditions to be met by the candidates shall be determined by a law;</li><!--Section: section/223, type: list-->
<li id="s223" data-link-target="s223" data-id="section/223" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="lhquota">First chamber representation quotas</span>
</div>Half of the members of the People’s Assembly at least shall be of the workers and farmers, and the law shall state the definition of the worker and the farmer.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/225, type: title-->
<div id="s225" data-link-target="s225" data-id="section/225" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 61</h3><!--Section: section/226, type: body-->
<div id="s226" data-link-target="s226" data-id="section/226" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The Election Law shall include the provisions that ensure:</p><!--Section: section/227, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s227" data-link-target="s227" data-id="section/227" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The freedom of voters to choose their representatives and the safety and integrity of the electoral procedures;</li><!--Section: section/229, type: list-->
<li id="s229" data-link-target="s229" data-id="section/229" style="list-style-type: '2. '">The right of candidates to supervise the electoral process;</li><!--Section: section/231, type: list-->
<li id="s231" data-link-target="s231" data-id="section/231" style="list-style-type: '3. '">Punishing those who abuse the will of the voters;</li><!--Section: section/233, type: list-->
<li id="s233" data-link-target="s233" data-id="section/233" style="list-style-type: '4. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="camppubf">Campaign financing</span>
</div>Identifying the regulations of financing election campaigns;</li><!--Section: section/235, type: list-->
<li id="s235" data-link-target="s235" data-id="section/235" style="list-style-type: '5. '">Organizing the election campaign and the use of media outlets.</li></ol></div>
</div><!--Section: section/237, type: title-->
<div id="s237" data-link-target="s237" data-id="section/237" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 62</h3><!--Section: section/238, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s238" data-link-target="s238" data-id="section/238" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="electsch">Scheduling of elections</span>
</div>Elections shall be held during the sixty days preceding the expiry date of the mandate of the People’s Assembly term;</li><!--Section: section/240, type: list-->
<li id="s240" data-link-target="s240" data-id="section/240" style="list-style-type: '2. '">The People’s Assembly shall continue its meetings if no other Assembly is elected and it shall remain in place until a new Assembly is elected.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/242, type: title-->
<div id="s242" data-link-target="s242" data-id="section/242" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="remleg">Removal of individual legislators</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="legrep">Replacement of legislators</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 63</h3><!--Section: section/243, type: body-->
<div id="s243" data-link-target="s243" data-id="section/243" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">If the membership of a member of the People’s Assembly is vacant for some reason, an alternative shall be elected within sixty days from the date of the membership vacancy, provided that the remaining term of the Assembly is no less than six months. The membership of the new member shall end by the expiry date of the mandate of the Assembly’s term, and the Election Law shall determine the cases of vacant membership.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/244, type: title-->
<div id="s244" data-link-target="s244" data-id="section/244" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 64</h3><!--Section: section/245, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s245" data-link-target="s245" data-id="section/245" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The People’s Assembly shall be called to convene by a decree issued by the President of the Republic within fifteen days from the expiry date of the mandate of the existing Assembly or from the date of announcing the election results in case of not having such an Assembly. The People’s Assembly shall be definitely convened on the sixteenth day if the call-to-convene decree is not issued;</li><!--Section: section/247, type: list-->
<li id="s247" data-link-target="s247" data-id="section/247" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="lhlead">Leader of first chamber</span>
</div>The Assembly shall elect, at its first meeting, its speaker and members who shall be annually re-elected.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/249, type: title-->
<div id="s249" data-link-target="s249" data-id="section/249" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 65</h3><!--Section: section/250, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s250" data-link-target="s250" data-id="section/250" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="session">Length of legislative sessions</span>
</div>The Assembly shall call for three regular sessions per year; the total of which should not be less than six months, and the Assembly’s rules of procedure shall set the time and duration of each of them;</li><!--Section: section/252, type: list-->
<li id="s252" data-link-target="s252" data-id="section/252" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="exsess">Extraordinary legislative sessions</span>
</div>The Assembly may be invited to extraordinary sessions upon the request of the President of the Republic, one third of the members of the Assembly or the Assembly’s office;</li><!--Section: section/254, type: list-->
<li id="s254" data-link-target="s254" data-id="section/254" style="list-style-type: '3. '">The last legislative session of the year shall remain open until the approval of the state budget.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/256, type: title-->
<div id="s256" data-link-target="s256" data-id="section/256" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="conpow">Constitutional court powers</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 66</h3><!--Section: section/257, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s257" data-link-target="s257" data-id="section/257" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The Supreme Constitutional Court shall have jurisdiction to consider appeals related to the elections of the members of the People’s Assembly.</li><!--Section: section/259, type: list-->
<li id="s259" data-link-target="s259" data-id="section/259" style="list-style-type: '2. '">Appeals shall be submitted by the candidate within three days from the date of announcing the results; and the court shall decide its final judgments within seven days from the expiry date of submitting appeals.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/261, type: title-->
<div id="s261" data-link-target="s261" data-id="section/261" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="oath">Oaths to abide by constitution</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 67</h3><!--Section: section/262, type: body-->
<div id="s262" data-link-target="s262" data-id="section/262" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Members of the People’s Assembly shall swear-in the constitutional oath mentioned in Article 7 of the Constitution.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/263, type: title-->
<div id="s263" data-link-target="s263" data-id="section/263" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="income">Compensation of legislators</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 68</h3><!--Section: section/264, type: body-->
<div id="s264" data-link-target="s264" data-id="section/264" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The emoluments and compensations of members of the People’s Assembly shall be determined by a law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/265, type: title-->
<div id="s265" data-link-target="s265" data-id="section/265" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 69</h3><!--Section: section/266, type: body-->
<div id="s266" data-link-target="s266" data-id="section/266" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The People’s Assembly shall put its rules of procedure to regulate the manner of working in it and the way of exercising its functions, and define terms of reference of the Assembly’ office.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/267, type: title-->
<div id="s267" data-link-target="s267" data-id="section/267" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="commit">Legislative committees</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="immunity">Immunity of legislators</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="pubmeet">Public or private sessions</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 70</h3><!--Section: section/268, type: body-->
<div id="s268" data-link-target="s268" data-id="section/268" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Members of the People’s Assembly shall not be questioned in a civil or criminal manner because of events or opinions they express or during a vote in public or private meetings and during the work of the committees.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/269, type: title-->
<div id="s269" data-link-target="s269" data-id="section/269" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="immunity">Immunity of legislators</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 71</h3><!--Section: section/270, type: body-->
<div id="s270" data-link-target="s270" data-id="section/270" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Members of the People’s Assembly shall enjoy immunity for the mandate duration of the Assembly. Criminal proceedings against any member of them shall be taken after having a prior permission from the Assembly unless caught in the act. In non-session cases, permission shall be taken from the Assembly’s office, and the Assembly shall be notified by any action taken at its first meeting.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/271, type: title-->
<div id="s271" data-link-target="s271" data-id="section/271" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="profleg">Outside professions of legislators</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 72</h3><!--Section: section/272, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s272" data-link-target="s272" data-id="section/272" style="list-style-type: '1. '">No member may take advantage of membership in any business;</li><!--Section: section/274, type: list-->
<li id="s274" data-link-target="s274" data-id="section/274" style="list-style-type: '2. '">The law shall specify the business which may not be combined with the membership in the Assembly.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/276, type: title-->
<div id="s276" data-link-target="s276" data-id="section/276" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 73</h3><!--Section: section/277, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s277" data-link-target="s277" data-id="section/277" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="lhlead">Leader of first chamber</span>
</div>The speaker of the People’s Assembly shall represent the Assembly, sign and speak on its behalf;</li><!--Section: section/279, type: list-->
<li id="s279" data-link-target="s279" data-id="section/279" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="milrest">Restrictions on the armed forces</span>
</div>The People’s Assembly shall have special guards under the authority of the Speaker of the Assembly; and no armed force may enter the Assembly without the permission of its Speaker.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/281, type: title-->
<div id="s281" data-link-target="s281" data-id="section/281" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="invexe">Legislative oversight of the executive</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="legini">Initiation of general legislation</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 74</h3><!--Section: section/282, type: body-->
<div id="s282" data-link-target="s282" data-id="section/282" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Members of the People’s Assembly shall exercise the right of proposing laws and directing questions and inquiries to the cabinet or a minister in accordance with the rules of procedure of the Assembly.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/283, type: title-->
<div id="s283" data-link-target="s283" data-id="section/283" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 75</h3><!--Section: section/284, type: body-->
<div id="s284" data-link-target="s284" data-id="section/284" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The People’s Assembly undertakes the following functions:</p><!--Section: section/285, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s285" data-link-target="s285" data-id="section/285" style="list-style-type: '1. '">Approval of laws;</li><!--Section: section/287, type: list-->
<li id="s287" data-link-target="s287" data-id="section/287" style="list-style-type: '2. '">Discussing the statement of the cabinet;</li><!--Section: section/289, type: list-->
<li id="s289" data-link-target="s289" data-id="section/289" style="list-style-type: '3. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabdiss">Cabinet removal</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hogdiss">Head of government removal</span>
</div>Perform a vote of no-confidence in the cabinet or a minister;</li><!--Section: section/291, type: list-->
<li id="s291" data-link-target="s291" data-id="section/291" style="list-style-type: '4. '">Approval of the general budget and final accounts;</li><!--Section: section/293, type: list-->
<li id="s293" data-link-target="s293" data-id="section/293" style="list-style-type: '5. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="econplan">Economic plans</span>
</div>Approval of development plans;</li><!--Section: section/295, type: list-->
<li id="s295" data-link-target="s295" data-id="section/295" style="list-style-type: '6. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="intlaw">International law</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="treat">Treaty ratification</span>
</div>Approval of international treaties and conventions related to the safety of the state, including treaties of peace, alliance and all treaties related to the rights of sovereignty or conventions which grant privileges to foreign companies or institutions as well as treaties and conventions entailing additional expenses not included in its budget; or treaties and conventions related to loans’ contract or that are contrary to the provisions of the laws in force and requires new legislation which should come into force;</li><!--Section: section/297, type: list-->
<li id="s297" data-link-target="s297" data-id="section/297" style="list-style-type: '7. '">Approval of a general amnesty;</li><!--Section: section/299, type: list-->
<li id="s299" data-link-target="s299" data-id="section/299" style="list-style-type: '8. '">Accepting or rejecting the resignation of one of the members of the Assembly.</li></ol></div>
</div><!--Section: section/301, type: title-->
<div id="s301" data-link-target="s301" data-id="section/301" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 76</h3><!--Section: section/302, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s302" data-link-target="s302" data-id="section/302" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The Prime Minister shall present the cabinet’s statement within thirty days from the date of its formation to the People’s Assembly for discussion;</li><!--Section: section/304, type: list-->
<li id="s304" data-link-target="s304" data-id="section/304" style="list-style-type: '2. '">The cabinet shall be responsible for the implementation of its statement before the People’s Assembly;</li><!--Section: section/306, type: list-->
<li id="s306" data-link-target="s306" data-id="section/306" style="list-style-type: '3. '">If the Assembly is not in a regular session, it shall be invited to convene an extraordinary session.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/308, type: title-->
<div id="s308" data-link-target="s308" data-id="section/308" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hogdiss">Head of government removal</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="cabdiss">Cabinet removal</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 77</h3><!--Section: section/309, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s309" data-link-target="s309" data-id="section/309" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="invexe">Legislative oversight of the executive</span>
</div>A vote of no-confidence can only be conducted after the cabinet or one of its ministers is questioned in the Assembly; a vote of no-confidence should be upon a proposal made by at least a fifth of the members of the People’s Assembly and it must be obtained with a majority of the members;</li><!--Section: section/311, type: list-->
<li id="s311" data-link-target="s311" data-id="section/311" style="list-style-type: '2. '">If a vote of no-confidence is obtained, the Prime Minister shall submit the cabinet’s resignation to the President, so should the minister who got a vote of no-confidence.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/313, type: title-->
<div id="s313" data-link-target="s313" data-id="section/313" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="commit">Legislative committees</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 78</h3><!--Section: section/314, type: body-->
<div id="s314" data-link-target="s314" data-id="section/314" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The Assembly might form temporary committees from among its members to collect information and find facts on the issues related to exercising its authorities.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/315, type: title-->
<div id="s315" data-link-target="s315" data-id="section/315" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="budget">Budget bills</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 79</h3><!--Section: section/316, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s316" data-link-target="s316" data-id="section/316" style="list-style-type: '1. '">For every fiscal year there shall be one budget; and the beginning of fiscal year shall be determined by a law;</li><!--Section: section/318, type: list-->
<li id="s318" data-link-target="s318" data-id="section/318" style="list-style-type: '2. '">The law states the method of preparing the state’s general budget;</li><!--Section: section/320, type: list-->
<li id="s320" data-link-target="s320" data-id="section/320" style="list-style-type: '3. '">The draft budget should be presented to the people’s Assembly at least two months before the beginning of the fiscal year.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/322, type: title-->
<div id="s322" data-link-target="s322" data-id="section/322" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="budget">Budget bills</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 80</h3><!--Section: section/323, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s323" data-link-target="s323" data-id="section/323" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The Assembly votes on the budget title by title; and the budget shall not enter into force unless approved by the Assembly;</li><!--Section: section/325, type: list-->
<li id="s325" data-link-target="s325" data-id="section/325" style="list-style-type: '2. '">If the Assembly did not complete the process of approving the budget until the beginning of the new fiscal year, the budget of the previous years is used until the new year budget is approved and the revenues are collected in accordance with the laws and regulations in force;</li><!--Section: section/327, type: list-->
<li id="s327" data-link-target="s327" data-id="section/327" style="list-style-type: '3. '">Appropriations cannot be transferred from one title to another except according to the provisions of the law;</li><!--Section: section/329, type: list-->
<li id="s329" data-link-target="s329" data-id="section/329" style="list-style-type: '4. '">The Assembly might not increase the estimates of total revenues or expenditures while examining the budget.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/331, type: title-->
<div id="s331" data-link-target="s331" data-id="section/331" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="budget">Budget bills</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 81</h3><!--Section: section/332, type: body-->
<div id="s332" data-link-target="s332" data-id="section/332" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The people’s Assembly might, after approving the budget, approve laws which could create new expenditures and new revenues to cover them.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/333, type: title-->
<div id="s333" data-link-target="s333" data-id="section/333" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 82</h3><!--Section: section/334, type: body-->
<div id="s334" data-link-target="s334" data-id="section/334" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The final accounts of the fiscal year shall be presented to the People’s Assembly within a period not longer than one year as of the end of this year. The final account is done by a law; and the same procedures in approving the budget apply to the final account period.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/335, type: title-->
<div id="s335" data-link-target="s335" data-id="section/335" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Chapter II. The Executive Authority</h3><!--Section: section/336, type: title-->
<div id="s336" data-link-target="s336" data-id="section/336" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">1. The President of the Republic</h3><!--Section: section/337, type: title-->
<div id="s337" data-link-target="s337" data-id="section/337" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="execnum">Name/structure of executive(s)</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 83</h3><!--Section: section/338, type: body-->
<div id="s338" data-link-target="s338" data-id="section/338" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic and the Prime Minister exercise executive authority on behalf of the people within the limits provided for in the constitution.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/339, type: title-->
<div id="s339" data-link-target="s339" data-id="section/339" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hosrest">Eligibility for head of state</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 84</h3><!--Section: section/340, type: body-->
<div id="s340" data-link-target="s340" data-id="section/340" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The candidate for the office of President of the Republic should:</p><!--Section: section/341, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s341" data-link-target="s341" data-id="section/341" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hosage">Minimum age of head of state</span>
</div>Have completed forty years of age;</li><!--Section: section/343, type: list-->
<li id="s343" data-link-target="s343" data-id="section/343" style="list-style-type: '2. '">Be of Syrian nationality by birth, of parents who are of Syrian nationality by birth;</li><!--Section: section/345, type: list-->
<li id="s345" data-link-target="s345" data-id="section/345" style="list-style-type: '3. '">Enjoy civil and political rights and not convicted of a dishonorable felony, even if he was reinstated;</li><!--Section: section/347, type: list-->
<li id="s347" data-link-target="s347" data-id="section/347" style="list-style-type: '4. '">Not be married to a non-Syrian wife;</li><!--Section: section/349, type: list-->
<li id="s349" data-link-target="s349" data-id="section/349" style="list-style-type: '5. '">Be a resident of the Syrian Arab Republic for no less than 10 years continuously upon being nominated.</li></ol></div>
</div><!--Section: section/351, type: title-->
<div id="s351" data-link-target="s351" data-id="section/351" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hoselect">Head of state selection</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 85</h3><!--Section: section/352, type: body-->
<div id="s352" data-link-target="s352" data-id="section/352" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The nomination of a candidate for the office of President of the Republic shall be as follows:</p><!--Section: section/353, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s353" data-link-target="s353" data-id="section/353" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="electsch">Scheduling of elections</span>
</div>The Speaker of the People’s Assembly calls for the election of the President of the Republic before the end of the term of office of the existing president by no less than 60 days and no more than 90 days;</li><!--Section: section/355, type: list-->
<li id="s355" data-link-target="s355" data-id="section/355" style="list-style-type: '2. '">The candidacy application shall be made to the Supreme Constitutional Court, and is entered in a special register, within 10 days of announcing the call for electing the president;</li><!--Section: section/357, type: list-->
<li id="s357" data-link-target="s357" data-id="section/357" style="list-style-type: '3. '">The candidacy application shall not be accepted unless the applicant has acquired the support of at least 35 members of the People’s Assembly; and no member of the assembly might support more than one candidate;</li><!--Section: section/359, type: list-->
<li id="s359" data-link-target="s359" data-id="section/359" style="list-style-type: '4. '">Applications shall be examined by the Supreme Constitutional Court; and should be ruled on within 5 days of the deadline for application;</li><!--Section: section/361, type: list-->
<li id="s361" data-link-target="s361" data-id="section/361" style="list-style-type: '5. '">If the conditions required for candidacy were met by only one candidate during the period set for applying, the Speaker of the people’s assembly should call for fresh nominations according to the same conditions.</li></ol></div>
</div><!--Section: section/363, type: title-->
<div id="s363" data-link-target="s363" data-id="section/363" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hoselect">Head of state selection</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 86</h3><!--Section: section/364, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s364" data-link-target="s364" data-id="section/364" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The President of the Republic shall be elected directly by the people;</li><!--Section: section/366, type: list-->
<li id="s366" data-link-target="s366" data-id="section/366" style="list-style-type: '2. '">The candidate who wins the election for the President of the Republic is the one who gets the absolute majority of those who take part in the elections. If no candidate receives that majority, a rerun is carried out between the two candidates who receive the largest number of votes;</li><!--Section: section/368, type: list-->
<li id="s368" data-link-target="s368" data-id="section/368" style="list-style-type: '3. '">The results shall be announced by the Speaker of the People’s Assembly.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/370, type: title-->
<div id="s370" data-link-target="s370" data-id="section/370" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 87</h3><!--Section: section/371, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s371" data-link-target="s371" data-id="section/371" style="list-style-type: '1. '">If the People’s Assembly was dissolved during the period set for electing a new President of the Republic, the existing President of the Republic continues to exercise his duties until after the new Assembly is elected and convened; and the new President of the Republic shall be elected within the 90 days which follow the date of convening this Assembly;</li><!--Section: section/373, type: list-->
<li id="s373" data-link-target="s373" data-id="section/373" style="list-style-type: '2. '">If the term of the President of the Republic finished and no new president was elected, the Existing President of the Republic continues to assume his duties until the new president is elected.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/375, type: title-->
<div id="s375" data-link-target="s375" data-id="section/375" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hosterml">Head of state term limits</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hosterm">Head of state term length</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 88</h3><!--Section: section/376, type: body-->
<div id="s376" data-link-target="s376" data-id="section/376" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic is elected for 7 years as of the end of the term of the existing President. The President can be elected for only one more successive term.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/377, type: title-->
<div id="s377" data-link-target="s377" data-id="section/377" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="conpow">Constitutional court powers</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 89</h3><!--Section: section/378, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s378" data-link-target="s378" data-id="section/378" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The Supreme Constitutional Court has the jurisdiction to examine the challenges to the election of the President of the Republic;</li><!--Section: section/380, type: list-->
<li id="s380" data-link-target="s380" data-id="section/380" style="list-style-type: '2. '">The challenges shall be made by the candidate within 3 days of announcing the results; and the court rules on them finally within 7 days of the end of the deadline for making the challenges.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/382, type: title-->
<div id="s382" data-link-target="s382" data-id="section/382" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="oath">Oaths to abide by constitution</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 90</h3><!--Section: section/383, type: body-->
<div id="s383" data-link-target="s383" data-id="section/383" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic shall be sworn in before the People’s Assembly before assuming his duties by repeating the constitutional oath mentioned in Article 7 of the Constitution.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/384, type: title-->
<div id="s384" data-link-target="s384" data-id="section/384" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="depexec">Deputy executive</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 91</h3><!--Section: section/385, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s385" data-link-target="s385" data-id="section/385" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The President of the Republic might name one or more deputies and delegate to them some of his authorities;</li><!--Section: section/387, type: list-->
<li id="s387" data-link-target="s387" data-id="section/387" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="oath">Oaths to abide by constitution</span>
</div>The Vice-president is sworn in before the President of the Republic by repeating the constitutional oath mentioned in Article 7 of the Constitution.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/389, type: title-->
<div id="s389" data-link-target="s389" data-id="section/389" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="depexec">Deputy executive</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 92</h3><!--Section: section/390, type: body-->
<div id="s390" data-link-target="s390" data-id="section/390" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">If an impediment prevented the President of the Republic from continuing to carry out his duties, the Vice-president shall deputize for him.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/391, type: title-->
<div id="s391" data-link-target="s391" data-id="section/391" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hossucc">Head of state replacement</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 93</h3><!--Section: section/392, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s392" data-link-target="s392" data-id="section/392" style="list-style-type: '1. '">If the office of the President of the Republic becomes vacant or if he is permanently incapacitated, the first Vice-president assumes the President’s duties for a period of no more than 90 days of the President of the Republic’s office becoming vacant. During this period new presidential elections shall be conducted;</li><!--Section: section/394, type: list-->
<li id="s394" data-link-target="s394" data-id="section/394" style="list-style-type: '2. '">If the office of the President of the Republic becomes vacant, and he does not have a Vice-president, his duties shall be assumed temporarily by the Prime Minister for a period of no more than 90 days of the date of the President of the Republic’s office becoming vacant. During this period new presidential elections shall be conducted.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/396, type: title-->
<div id="s396" data-link-target="s396" data-id="section/396" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 94</h3><!--Section: section/397, type: body-->
<div id="s397" data-link-target="s397" data-id="section/397" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">If the President of the Republic resigned from office, he should address the resignation letter to the People’s Assembly.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/398, type: title-->
<div id="s398" data-link-target="s398" data-id="section/398" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 95</h3><!--Section: section/399, type: body-->
<div id="s399" data-link-target="s399" data-id="section/399" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The protocol, privileges and allocations required for the office of President of the Republic shall be set out in a law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/400, type: title-->
<div id="s400" data-link-target="s400" data-id="section/400" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 96</h3><!--Section: section/401, type: body-->
<div id="s401" data-link-target="s401" data-id="section/401" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic shall insure respect for the Constitution, the regular running of public authorities, protection of national unity and survival of the state.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/402, type: title-->
<div id="s402" data-link-target="s402" data-id="section/402" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabdiss">Cabinet removal</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hogelect">Head of government selection</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="cabsel">Cabinet selection</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hogdiss">Head of government removal</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 97</h3><!--Section: section/403, type: body-->
<div id="s403" data-link-target="s403" data-id="section/403" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic shall name the Prime Minister, his deputies, ministers and their deputies, accept their resignation and dismiss them from office.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/404, type: title-->
<div id="s404" data-link-target="s404" data-id="section/404" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hospow">Head of state powers</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 98</h3><!--Section: section/405, type: body-->
<div id="s405" data-link-target="s405" data-id="section/405" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">In a meeting chaired by him, the President of the Republic lays down the general policy of the state and oversees its implementation.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/406, type: title-->
<div id="s406" data-link-target="s406" data-id="section/406" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hospow">Head of state powers</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 99</h3><!--Section: section/407, type: body-->
<div id="s407" data-link-target="s407" data-id="section/407" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic might call the Council of Ministers to a meeting chaired by him; and might ask for reports from the Prime Minister and the ministers.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/408, type: title-->
<div id="s408" data-link-target="s408" data-id="section/408" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="legapp">Approval or veto of general legislation</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="override">Veto override procedure</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 100</h3><!--Section: section/409, type: body-->
<div id="s409" data-link-target="s409" data-id="section/409" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic shall pass the laws approved by the People’s Assembly. He might also reject them through a justified decision within one month of these laws being received by the Presidency. If they are approved a second time by the People’s Assembly with a two thirds majority, they shall be passed by the President of the Republic.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/410, type: title-->
<div id="s410" data-link-target="s410" data-id="section/410" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hosdec">Head of state decree power</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 101</h3><!--Section: section/411, type: body-->
<div id="s411" data-link-target="s411" data-id="section/411" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic shall pass decrees, decisions and orders in accordance with the laws.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/412, type: title-->
<div id="s412" data-link-target="s412" data-id="section/412" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="war">Power to declare/approve war</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hospow">Head of state powers</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="comchief">Designation of commander in chief</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 102</h3><!--Section: section/413, type: body-->
<div id="s413" data-link-target="s413" data-id="section/413" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic declares war, calls for general mobilization and concludes peace agreements after obtaining the approval of the People’s Assembly.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/414, type: title-->
<div id="s414" data-link-target="s414" data-id="section/414" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="em">Emergency provisions</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hosdec">Head of state decree power</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 103</h3><!--Section: section/415, type: body-->
<div id="s415" data-link-target="s415" data-id="section/415" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic declares the state of emergency and repeals it in a decree taken at the Council of Ministers chaired by him with a two thirds majority, provided that the decree is presented to the People’s Assembly in its first session. The law sets out the relevant provisions.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/416, type: title-->
<div id="s416" data-link-target="s416" data-id="section/416" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hospow">Head of state powers</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="headforn">Foreign affairs representative</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 104</h3><!--Section: section/417, type: body-->
<div id="s417" data-link-target="s417" data-id="section/417" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic accredits heads of diplomatic missions in foreign countries and accepts the credentials of heads of foreign diplomatic missions in the Syrian Arab Republic.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/418, type: title-->
<div id="s418" data-link-target="s418" data-id="section/418" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="comchief">Designation of commander in chief</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 105</h3><!--Section: section/419, type: body-->
<div id="s419" data-link-target="s419" data-id="section/419" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic is the Commander in Chief of the army and armed forces; and he issues all the decisions necessary to exercise this authority. He might delegate some of these authorities.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/420, type: title-->
<div id="s420" data-link-target="s420" data-id="section/420" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="milcom">Selection of active-duty commanders</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hospow">Head of state powers</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 106</h3><!--Section: section/421, type: body-->
<div id="s421" data-link-target="s421" data-id="section/421" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic appoints civilian and military employees and ends their services in accordance with the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/422, type: title-->
<div id="s422" data-link-target="s422" data-id="section/422" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="treat">Treaty ratification</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="intlaw">International law</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 107</h3><!--Section: section/423, type: body-->
<div id="s423" data-link-target="s423" data-id="section/423" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic concludes international treaties and agreements and revokes them in accordance with provisions of the Constitution and rules of international law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/424, type: title-->
<div id="s424" data-link-target="s424" data-id="section/424" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="pardon">Power to pardon</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 108</h3><!--Section: section/425, type: body-->
<div id="s425" data-link-target="s425" data-id="section/425" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic grants special amnesty and might reinstate individuals.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/426, type: title-->
<div id="s426" data-link-target="s426" data-id="section/426" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hospow">Head of state powers</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 109</h3><!--Section: section/427, type: body-->
<div id="s427" data-link-target="s427" data-id="section/427" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic has the right to award medals and honors.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/428, type: title-->
<div id="s428" data-link-target="s428" data-id="section/428" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 110</h3><!--Section: section/429, type: body-->
<div id="s429" data-link-target="s429" data-id="section/429" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic might address letters to the People’s Assembly and make statements before it.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/430, type: title-->
<div id="s430" data-link-target="s430" data-id="section/430" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="legdiss">Dismissal of the legislature</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 111</h3><!--Section: section/431, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s431" data-link-target="s431" data-id="section/431" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The President of the Republic might decide to dissolve the People’s Assembly in a justified decision he makes;</li><!--Section: section/433, type: list-->
<li id="s433" data-link-target="s433" data-id="section/433" style="list-style-type: '2. '">Elections for a new People’s Assembly shall be conducted within 60 days of the date of dissolution;</li><!--Section: section/435, type: list-->
<li id="s435" data-link-target="s435" data-id="section/435" style="list-style-type: '3. '">The People’s Assembly might not be dissolved more than once for the same reason.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/437, type: title-->
<div id="s437" data-link-target="s437" data-id="section/437" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="legini">Initiation of general legislation</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 112</h3><!--Section: section/438, type: body-->
<div id="s438" data-link-target="s438" data-id="section/438" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic might prepare draft laws and refer them to the People’s Assembly to consider them for approval.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/439, type: title-->
<div id="s439" data-link-target="s439" data-id="section/439" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hosdec">Head of state decree power</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 113</h3><!--Section: section/440, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s440" data-link-target="s440" data-id="section/440" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The President of the Republic assumes the authority of legislation when the People’s Assembly is not in session, or during sessions if absolute necessity requires this, or in the period during which the Assembly is dissolved.</li><!--Section: section/442, type: list-->
<li id="s442" data-link-target="s442" data-id="section/442" style="list-style-type: '2. '">These legislation shall be referred to the Assembly within 15 days of its first session;</li><!--Section: section/444, type: list-->
<li id="s444" data-link-target="s444" data-id="section/444" style="list-style-type: '3. '">The Assembly has the right to revoke such legislation or amend them in a law with a majority of two thirds of the members registered for attending the session, provided it is no less than the absolute majority of all its members. Such amendment or revocation shall not have a retroactive effect. If they are not amended or revoked, they shall be considered approved.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/446, type: title-->
<div id="s446" data-link-target="s446" data-id="section/446" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="em">Emergency provisions</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 114</h3><!--Section: section/447, type: body-->
<div id="s447" data-link-target="s447" data-id="section/447" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">If a grave danger and a situation threatening national unity, the safety and integrity of the territories of the homeland occurs, or prevents state institutions from shouldering their constitutional responsibilities, the President of the Republic might take the quick measures necessitated by these circumstances to face that danger.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/448, type: title-->
<div id="s448" data-link-target="s448" data-id="section/448" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hospow">Head of state powers</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hosstaff">Advisory bodies to the head of state</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 115</h3><!--Section: section/449, type: body-->
<div id="s449" data-link-target="s449" data-id="section/449" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic might set up special bodies, councils and committees whose tasks and mandates are set out in the decisions taken to create them.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/450, type: title-->
<div id="s450" data-link-target="s450" data-id="section/450" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="referen">Referenda</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 116</h3><!--Section: section/451, type: body-->
<div id="s451" data-link-target="s451" data-id="section/451" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic might call for a referendum on important issues which affect the higher interests of the country. The result of the referendum shall be binding and come into force as of the date of its announcement; and it shall be published by the President of the Republic.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/452, type: title-->
<div id="s452" data-link-target="s452" data-id="section/452" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hosdiss">Head of state removal</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hosimm">Head of state immunity</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 117</h3><!--Section: section/453, type: body-->
<div id="s453" data-link-target="s453" data-id="section/453" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Republic is not responsible for the acts he does in carrying out his duties except in the case of high treason; and the accusation should be made through a People’s Assembly decision taken by the Assembly in a public vote and with a two thirds majority in a secret session based on a proposal made by at least one third of the members. He shall be tried before the Supreme Constitutional Court.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/454, type: title-->
<div id="s454" data-link-target="s454" data-id="section/454" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabinet">Establishment of cabinet/ministers</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">2. The Council of Ministers</h3><!--Section: section/455, type: title-->
<div id="s455" data-link-target="s455" data-id="section/455" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 118</h3><!--Section: section/456, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s456" data-link-target="s456" data-id="section/456" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabpow">Powers of cabinet</span>
</div>The Council of Ministers is the highest executive and administrative authority of the state. It consists of the Prime Minister, his deputies and the ministers. It supervises the implementation of the laws and regulations and oversees the work of state institutions;</li><!--Section: section/458, type: list-->
<li id="s458" data-link-target="s458" data-id="section/458" style="list-style-type: '2. '">The Prime Minister supervises the work of his deputies and the ministers.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/460, type: title-->
<div id="s460" data-link-target="s460" data-id="section/460" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 119</h3><!--Section: section/461, type: body-->
<div id="s461" data-link-target="s461" data-id="section/461" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The allocations and benefits of the Prime Minister, his deputies and the ministers shall be set out in a law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/462, type: title-->
<div id="s462" data-link-target="s462" data-id="section/462" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="oath">Oaths to abide by constitution</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 120</h3><!--Section: section/463, type: body-->
<div id="s463" data-link-target="s463" data-id="section/463" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The Prime Minister, his deputies and the ministers shall be sworn in before the President of the Republic when a new government is formed by repeating the constitutional oath mentioned in Article 7 of the Constitution before they start their work. When the government is reshuffled, only the new ministers shall be sworn in.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/464, type: title-->
<div id="s464" data-link-target="s464" data-id="section/464" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 121</h3><!--Section: section/465, type: body-->
<div id="s465" data-link-target="s465" data-id="section/465" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The Prime Minister, his deputies and the ministers shall be responsible before the President of the Republic and the People’s Assembly.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/466, type: title-->
<div id="s466" data-link-target="s466" data-id="section/466" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 122</h3><!--Section: section/467, type: body-->
<div id="s467" data-link-target="s467" data-id="section/467" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The minister is the highest administrative authority in his ministry, and he shall implement the state’s public policy in relation to his ministry.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/468, type: title-->
<div id="s468" data-link-target="s468" data-id="section/468" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 123</h3><!--Section: section/469, type: body-->
<div id="s469" data-link-target="s469" data-id="section/469" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">While in office, ministers shall be barred from being members of the boards of private companies or agents for such companies and from carrying out, directly or indirectly, any commercial activity or private profession.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/470, type: title-->
<div id="s470" data-link-target="s470" data-id="section/470" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabdiss">Cabinet removal</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hogdiss">Head of government removal</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 124</h3><!--Section: section/471, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s471" data-link-target="s471" data-id="section/471" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The Prime Minister, his deputies and the ministers shall be responsible for their acts, from a civil and penal perspective, in accordance with the law;</li><!--Section: section/473, type: list-->
<li id="s473" data-link-target="s473" data-id="section/473" style="list-style-type: '2. '">The President of the Republic has the right to refer the Prime Minister, his deputies and the ministers to the courts for any crimes any of them commits while in office or because of such crimes;</li><!--Section: section/475, type: list-->
<li id="s475" data-link-target="s475" data-id="section/475" style="list-style-type: '3. '">The accused shall be suspended from office as soon as an indictment is made until a ruling is passed on the accusation made against him. His resignation or dismissal does not prevent his trial. Procedures are conducted as stated in the law.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/477, type: title-->
<div id="s477" data-link-target="s477" data-id="section/477" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 125</h3><!--Section: section/478, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s478" data-link-target="s478" data-id="section/478" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The cabinet shall be considered as resigned in the following cases:<!--Section: section/480, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s480" data-link-target="s480" data-id="section/480" style="list-style-type: 'a. '">Upon the end of the term of office of the President of the Republic;</li><!--Section: section/482, type: list-->
<li id="s482" data-link-target="s482" data-id="section/482" style="list-style-type: 'b. '">Upon the election of a new People’s Assembly;</li><!--Section: section/484, type: list-->
<li id="s484" data-link-target="s484" data-id="section/484" style="list-style-type: 'c. '">If the majority of the ministers resigned.</li></ol></li><!--Section: section/486, type: list-->
<li id="s486" data-link-target="s486" data-id="section/486" style="list-style-type: '2. '">The cabinet carries on in a care taker capacity until a decree is passed naming a new cabinet.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/488, type: title-->
<div id="s488" data-link-target="s488" data-id="section/488" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hoglegr">Head of government's role in the legislature</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="cabrest">Eligibility for cabinet</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 126</h3><!--Section: section/489, type: body-->
<div id="s489" data-link-target="s489" data-id="section/489" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">An individual can be a minister and a member of the People’s Assembly at the same time.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/490, type: title-->
<div id="s490" data-link-target="s490" data-id="section/490" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 127</h3><!--Section: section/491, type: body-->
<div id="s491" data-link-target="s491" data-id="section/491" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">Provisions applying to ministers apply to deputy ministers.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/492, type: title-->
<div id="s492" data-link-target="s492" data-id="section/492" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabpow">Powers of cabinet</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 128</h3><!--Section: section/493, type: body-->
<div id="s493" data-link-target="s493" data-id="section/493" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The mandate of the Council of Ministers is as follows:</p><!--Section: section/494, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s494" data-link-target="s494" data-id="section/494" style="list-style-type: '1. '">It draws the executive plans of the state’s general policy;</li><!--Section: section/496, type: list-->
<li id="s496" data-link-target="s496" data-id="section/496" style="list-style-type: '2. '">It guides the work of ministers and other public bodies;</li><!--Section: section/498, type: list-->
<li id="s498" data-link-target="s498" data-id="section/498" style="list-style-type: '3. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="budget">Budget bills</span>
</div>It draws the state’s draft budget;</li><!--Section: section/500, type: list-->
<li id="s500" data-link-target="s500" data-id="section/500" style="list-style-type: '4. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="legini">Initiation of general legislation</span>
</div>It drafts laws;</li><!--Section: section/502, type: list-->
<li id="s502" data-link-target="s502" data-id="section/502" style="list-style-type: '5. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="econplan">Economic plans</span>
</div>It prepares development plans and plans for upgrading production and the exploitation of national resources and everything that could support and develop the economy and increase national income;</li><!--Section: section/504, type: list-->
<li id="s504" data-link-target="s504" data-id="section/504" style="list-style-type: '6. '">It concludes loan contracts and grants loans in accordance with provisions of the constitution;</li><!--Section: section/506, type: list-->
<li id="s506" data-link-target="s506" data-id="section/506" style="list-style-type: '7. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="treat">Treaty ratification</span>
</div>Concludes treaties and agreements in accordance with provisions of the constitution;</li><!--Section: section/508, type: list-->
<li id="s508" data-link-target="s508" data-id="section/508" style="list-style-type: '8. '">Follows up on enforcing the laws and protects the interests and the security of the state and protects the freedoms and rights of the population;</li><!--Section: section/510, type: list-->
<li id="s510" data-link-target="s510" data-id="section/510" style="list-style-type: '9. '">Passes administrative decisions in accordance with the laws and regulations and oversees their implementation.</li></ol></div>
</div><!--Section: section/512, type: title-->
<div id="s512" data-link-target="s512" data-id="section/512" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 129</h3><!--Section: section/513, type: body-->
<div id="s513" data-link-target="s513" data-id="section/513" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The Prime Minister and the ministers exercise the authorities provided for in the laws in force in a manner that does not contravene the authorities given to other authorities in the Constitution, in addition to the other authorities stated in its provisions.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/514, type: title-->
<div id="s514" data-link-target="s514" data-id="section/514" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="mun">Municipal government</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">3. Local Councils</h3><!--Section: section/515, type: title-->
<div id="s515" data-link-target="s515" data-id="section/515" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 130</h3><!--Section: section/516, type: body-->
<div id="s516" data-link-target="s516" data-id="section/516" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The Syrian Arab Republic consists of administrative units; and the law states their number, boundaries, authorities and the extent to which they enjoy the status of a legal entity, financial and administrative independence.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/517, type: title-->
<div id="s517" data-link-target="s517" data-id="section/517" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 131</h3><!--Section: section/518, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s518" data-link-target="s518" data-id="section/518" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The organization of local administration units is based on applying the principle of decentralization of authorities and responsibilities. The law states the relationship between these units and the central authority, their mandate, financial revenues and control over their work. It also states the way their heads are appointed or elected, their authorities and the authorities of heads of sectors.</li><!--Section: section/520, type: list-->
<li id="s520" data-link-target="s520" data-id="section/520" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="freeelec">Secret ballot</span>
</div>Local administration units shall have councils elected in a general, secret, direct and equal manner.</li></ol></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/522, type: title-->
<div id="s522" data-link-target="s522" data-id="section/522" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Chapter III. The Judicial Authority</h3><!--Section: section/523, type: title-->
<div id="s523" data-link-target="s523" data-id="section/523" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">1. The Courts and Attorney General’s Office</h3><!--Section: section/524, type: title-->
<div id="s524" data-link-target="s524" data-id="section/524" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="judind">Judicial independence</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="jc">Establishment of judicial council</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 132</h3><!--Section: section/525, type: body-->
<div id="s525" data-link-target="s525" data-id="section/525" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The judicial authority is independent; and the President of the Republic insures this independence assisted by the Supreme Judicial Council.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/526, type: title-->
<div id="s526" data-link-target="s526" data-id="section/526" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="jc">Establishment of judicial council</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 133</h3><!--Section: section/527, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s527" data-link-target="s527" data-id="section/527" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The Supreme Judicial Council is headed by the President of the Republic; and the law states the way it shall be formed, its mandate and its rules of procedures;</li><!--Section: section/529, type: list-->
<li id="s529" data-link-target="s529" data-id="section/529" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="judind">Judicial independence</span>
</div>The Supreme Judicial Council insures the provision of the guarantees necessary for the independence of the judiciary.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/531, type: title-->
<div id="s531" data-link-target="s531" data-id="section/531" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 134</h3><!--Section: section/532, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s532" data-link-target="s532" data-id="section/532" style="list-style-type: '1. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="judind">Judicial independence</span>
</div>Judges are independent and there is no authority over them except that of the law;</li><!--Section: section/534, type: list-->
<li id="s534" data-link-target="s534" data-id="section/534" style="list-style-type: '2. '">The judges’ honor, conscience and impartiality constitute the guarantees for people’s rights and freedoms.</li></ol></div><!--Section: section/536, type: title-->
<div id="s536" data-link-target="s536" data-id="section/536" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="levjud">Structure of the courts</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 135</h3><!--Section: section/537, type: body-->
<div id="s537" data-link-target="s537" data-id="section/537" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The law regulates the different branches, categories and degrees of the judicial system. It also states the rules for the mandates of different courts.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/538, type: title-->
<div id="s538" data-link-target="s538" data-id="section/538" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="jrem">Supreme/ordinary court judge removal</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 136</h3><!--Section: section/539, type: body-->
<div id="s539" data-link-target="s539" data-id="section/539" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The law states the conditions for appointing judges, promoting, transferring, disciplining and dismissing them.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/540, type: title-->
<div id="s540" data-link-target="s540" data-id="section/540" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="atgen">Attorney general</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 137</h3><!--Section: section/541, type: body-->
<div id="s541" data-link-target="s541" data-id="section/541" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The Attorney General’s Office is a single judicial institution headed by the Minister of Justice. The law regulates its function and mandate.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/542, type: title-->
<div id="s542" data-link-target="s542" data-id="section/542" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 138</h3><!--Section: section/543, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s543" data-link-target="s543" data-id="section/543" style="list-style-type: '1. '">Judicial rulings are made in the name of the Arab people of Syria;</li><!--Section: section/545, type: list-->
<li id="s545" data-link-target="s545" data-id="section/545" style="list-style-type: '2. '">Not implementing judicial rulings or obstructing their implementation is a crime punished in accordance with provisions of the law.</li></ol></div>
</div><!--Section: section/547, type: title-->
<div id="s547" data-link-target="s547" data-id="section/547" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">2. Administrative Judiciary</h3><!--Section: section/548, type: title-->
<div id="s548" data-link-target="s548" data-id="section/548" class="section article-list level3 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="adres">Eligibility for administrative  judges</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="adsel">Administrative court selection</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="adterm">Administrative court term length</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="judcrts1">Establishment of administrative courts</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="adtermn">Administrative court term limits</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="adage">Min age of administrative judges</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-3">Article 139</h3><!--Section: section/549, type: body-->
<div id="s549" data-link-target="s549" data-id="section/549" class="section article-list level4 article-body"><p class="content">The State’s Council is in charge of Administrative Judiciary. It is an independent judicial and advisory body. The law states its mandate and conditions for appointing, promoting, transferring, disciplining and dismissing them.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/550, type: title-->
<div id="s550" data-link-target="s550" data-id="section/550" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="judcrts2">Establishment of constitutional court</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-0">Title IV. The Supreme Constitutional Court</h3><!--Section: section/551, type: title-->
<div id="s551" data-link-target="s551" data-id="section/551" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 140</h3><!--Section: section/552, type: body-->
<div id="s552" data-link-target="s552" data-id="section/552" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Supreme Constitutional Court is an independent judicial body based in Damascus.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/553, type: title-->
<div id="s553" data-link-target="s553" data-id="section/553" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="consel">Constitutional court selection</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 141</h3><!--Section: section/554, type: body-->
<div id="s554" data-link-target="s554" data-id="section/554" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Supreme Constitutional Court consists of at least seven members, one of them shall be named president in a decree passed by the President of the Republic.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/555, type: title-->
<div id="s555" data-link-target="s555" data-id="section/555" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="profleg">Outside professions of legislators</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 142</h3><!--Section: section/556, type: body-->
<div id="s556" data-link-target="s556" data-id="section/556" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">An individual cannot be a member of the Supreme Constitutional Court and a minister or a member of the People’s Assembly at the same time. The law states the other jobs that cannot be done by a member of the Court.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/557, type: title-->
<div id="s557" data-link-target="s557" data-id="section/557" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="conterm">Constitutional court term length</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 143</h3><!--Section: section/558, type: body-->
<div id="s558" data-link-target="s558" data-id="section/558" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The duration of membership of the Supreme Constitutional Court shall be four years renewable.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/559, type: title-->
<div id="s559" data-link-target="s559" data-id="section/559" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="conrem">Constitutional court removal</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 144</h3><!--Section: section/560, type: body-->
<div id="s560" data-link-target="s560" data-id="section/560" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Members of the Supreme Constitutional Court cannot be dismissed from its membership except in accordance with the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/561, type: title-->
<div id="s561" data-link-target="s561" data-id="section/561" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="god">God or other deities</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="oath">Oaths to abide by constitution</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 145</h3><!--Section: section/562, type: body-->
<div id="s562" data-link-target="s562" data-id="section/562" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">President and members of the Supreme Constitutional Court shall be sworn in before the President of the Republic in the presence of the Speaker of the People’s Assembly before they assume their duties. They repeat the following oath: “I swear by the Great Almighty to respect the Constitution and the laws of the country and to carry out my responsibilities with integrity and impartiality”.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/563, type: title-->
<div id="s563" data-link-target="s563" data-id="section/563" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="interp">Constitutional interpretation</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="conpow">Constitutional court powers</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 146</h3><!--Section: section/564, type: body-->
<div id="s564" data-link-target="s564" data-id="section/564" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The mandate of the Supreme Constitutional Court is as follows:</p><!--Section: section/565, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s565" data-link-target="s565" data-id="section/565" style="list-style-type: '1. '">Control over the constitutionality of the laws, legislative decrees, bylaws and regulations;</li><!--Section: section/567, type: list-->
<li id="s567" data-link-target="s567" data-id="section/567" style="list-style-type: '2. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="uncon">Constitutionality of legislation</span>
</div>Expressing opinion, upon the request of the President of the Republic, on the constitutionality of the draft laws and legislative decrees and the legality of draft decrees;</li><!--Section: section/569, type: list-->
<li id="s569" data-link-target="s569" data-id="section/569" style="list-style-type: '3. '">Supervising the election of the President of the Republic and organizing the relevant procedures;</li><!--Section: section/571, type: list-->
<li id="s571" data-link-target="s571" data-id="section/571" style="list-style-type: '4. '">Considering the challenges made to the soundness of the measures of electing the President of the Republic and members of the People’s Assembly and ruling on these challenges;</li><!--Section: section/573, type: list-->
<li id="s573" data-link-target="s573" data-id="section/573" style="list-style-type: '5. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hosdiss">Head of state removal</span>
</div>Trying the President of the Republic in the case of high treason;</li><!--Section: section/575, type: list-->
<li id="s575" data-link-target="s575" data-id="section/575" style="list-style-type: '6. '">The law states its other authorities.</li></ol></div>
</div><!--Section: section/577, type: title-->
<div id="s577" data-link-target="s577" data-id="section/577" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="uncon">Constitutionality of legislation</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 147</h3><!--Section: section/578, type: body-->
<div id="s578" data-link-target="s578" data-id="section/578" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Supreme Constitutional Court is charged with control over the constitutionality of the laws as follows:</p><!--Section: section/579, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s579" data-link-target="s579" data-id="section/579" style="list-style-type: '1. '">Consider the unconstitutionality of the law and decide according to the following:<!--Section: section/581, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s581" data-link-target="s581" data-id="section/581" style="list-style-type: 'a. '">If the President of the Republic or a fifth of the members of the People’s Assembly object to a law before it is passed, on the grounds of its unconstitutionality, it shall be suspended until the Court rules on it within 15 days of the date of lodging the objection at the Court. If the law is urgently needed, the Court shall rule on it within 7 days;</li><!--Section: section/583, type: list-->
<li id="s583" data-link-target="s583" data-id="section/583" style="list-style-type: 'b. '">If a fifth of the members of the People’s Assembly object to a legislative decree, on the grounds of its unconstitutionality within 15 days of it is being presented to the Assembly, the Court shall rule on it within 15 days of lodging the objection at the Court;</li><!--Section: section/585, type: list-->
<li id="s585" data-link-target="s585" data-id="section/585" style="list-style-type: 'c. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hosdec">Head of state decree power</span>
</div>If the Court ruled that the law, the legislative decree or the bylaw was unconstitutional, the items found to be unconstitutional shall be annulled with retroactive effect and all their consequences shall be removed.</li></ol></li><!--Section: section/587, type: list-->
<li id="s587" data-link-target="s587" data-id="section/587" style="list-style-type: '2. '">Considering the claim of the unconstitutionality of a law or a legislative decree and ruling on it takes place as follows:<!--Section: section/589, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s589" data-link-target="s589" data-id="section/589" style="list-style-type: 'a. '">If an opponent making a challenge claimed the unconstitutionality of a legal text applied by the court whose ruling is being challenged, and if the court considering the challenge found that the claim was serious and should be ruled on, it halts the proceedings of the case and refers it to the Supreme Constitutional Court;</li><!--Section: section/591, type: list-->
<li id="s591" data-link-target="s591" data-id="section/591" style="list-style-type: 'b. '">The Supreme Constitutional Court shall rule on the claim within 30 days of being entered in its register.</li></ol></li></ol></div>
</div><!--Section: section/593, type: title-->
<div id="s593" data-link-target="s593" data-id="section/593" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="referen">Referenda</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 148</h3><!--Section: section/594, type: body-->
<div id="s594" data-link-target="s594" data-id="section/594" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Supreme Constitutional Court shall not consider the constitutionality of the laws put by the President of the Republic to a referendum and obtained the approval of the people.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/595, type: title-->
<div id="s595" data-link-target="s595" data-id="section/595" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="conage">Min age of const court judges</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="conres">Eligibility for const court judges</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 149</h3><!--Section: section/596, type: body-->
<div id="s596" data-link-target="s596" data-id="section/596" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The law regulates the principles of considering and ruling on the issues under the mandate of the Supreme Constitutional Court. The law states the number of its staff and the conditions which need to be met by its members. It also states their immunity, responsibilities, salaries and privileges.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/597, type: title-->
<div id="s597" data-link-target="s597" data-id="section/597" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="amend">Constitution amendment procedure</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-0">Title V. Amending the Constitution</h3><!--Section: section/598, type: title-->
<div id="s598" data-link-target="s598" data-id="section/598" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 150</h3><!--Section: section/599, type: list-->
<ol><li id="s599" data-link-target="s599" data-id="section/599" style="list-style-type: '1. '">The President of the Republic, and so does a third of the members of the People’s Assembly, might propose amending the Constitution;</li><!--Section: section/601, type: list-->
<li id="s601" data-link-target="s601" data-id="section/601" style="list-style-type: '2. '">The proposal for amending the Constitution shall state the text proposed to be amended and the reasons for making the amendment;</li><!--Section: section/603, type: list-->
<li id="s603" data-link-target="s603" data-id="section/603" style="list-style-type: '3. '">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="commit">Legislative committees</span>
</div>As soon as the People’s Assembly receives the proposal for amendment, it sets up a special committee to examine it.</li><!--Section: section/605, type: list-->
<li id="s605" data-link-target="s605" data-id="section/605" style="list-style-type: '4. '">The Assembly discusses the proposal for amendment. If it approved it with a three quarters majority, the amendment shall be considered final provided that it is also approved by the President of the Republic.</li></ol></div>
</div><!--Section: section/607, type: title-->
<div id="s607" data-link-target="s607" data-id="section/607" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="tranprov">Transitional provisions</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-0">Title VI. General and Transitional Provisions</h3><!--Section: section/608, type: title-->
<div id="s608" data-link-target="s608" data-id="section/608" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 151</h3><!--Section: section/609, type: body-->
<div id="s609" data-link-target="s609" data-id="section/609" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Preamble of the Constitution is considered part and parcel of the Constitution</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/610, type: title-->
<div id="s610" data-link-target="s610" data-id="section/610" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="lhrest">Eligibility for first chamber</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hosrest">Eligibility for head of state</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hogrest">Eligibility for head of government</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="conres">Eligibility for const court judges</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="depexec">Deputy executive</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="cabrest">Eligibility for cabinet</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 152</h3><!--Section: section/611, type: body-->
<div id="s611" data-link-target="s611" data-id="section/611" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">No person carrying another nationality, in addition to the nationality of the Syrian Arab Republic, might occupy the office of President of the Republic, Vice-president, Prime Minister, deputy prime ministers, ministers, members of the People’s Assembly or members of the Supreme Constitutional Court.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/612, type: title-->
<div id="s612" data-link-target="s612" data-id="section/612" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 153</h3><!--Section: section/613, type: body-->
<div id="s613" data-link-target="s613" data-id="section/613" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">This constitution shall not be amended before 18 months of coming into force.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/614, type: title-->
<div id="s614" data-link-target="s614" data-id="section/614" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 154</h3><!--Section: section/615, type: body-->
<div id="s615" data-link-target="s615" data-id="section/615" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The legislation in force and passed before approving this Constitution remain in force until they are amended in accordance with its provisions, provided that the amendment is done within a period of no longer than 3 years.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/616, type: title-->
<div id="s616" data-link-target="s616" data-id="section/616" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 155</h3><!--Section: section/617, type: body-->
<div id="s617" data-link-target="s617" data-id="section/617" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The term of office of the current President of the Republic terminates after 7 years of his being sworn in as President. He has the right to stand again for the office of President of the Republic. Provisions of Article 88 of this Constitution apply to him as of the next presidential elections.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/618, type: title-->
<div id="s618" data-link-target="s618" data-id="section/618" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 156</h3><!--Section: section/619, type: body-->
<div id="s619" data-link-target="s619" data-id="section/619" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Elections for the first People’s Assembly under this Constitution shall be held within 90 days of the date of its being approved through referendum.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/620, type: title-->
<div id="s620" data-link-target="s620" data-id="section/620" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 157</h3><!--Section: section/621, type: body-->
<div id="s621" data-link-target="s621" data-id="section/621" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">This Constitution shall be published in the official bulletin and enters into force as of being approved.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

  </div>
</div>

